The paper proposes a graph neural network for predicting interactions between structured entities, which is a common task in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of graph convolution operations and long short-term memory networks suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), social and information networks (cs.SI), or computational linguistics (cs.CL).
